## 2. [Objectives & Success Metrics](#2-objectives--success-metrics)
#- **Purpose**: Why build this site? What user problems or gaps does it address?
#- **Goals**: e.g., help organizations crosswalk AI frameworks, deliver ready-to-use templates, introduce automation workflows.
#- **Success Metrics**: Monthly users, newsletter signups, template downloads, contributor count, assessment tool usage.
- **Simplify AI governance**: Provide clear crosswalks, summaries, and starting templates tailored to practitioner needs.
- **Enable self-service automation**: Support self-assessment, FAIR mini-quantification, model/system card generation.
- **Foster community engagement**: Encourage contributions, crosswalk improvements, and ownership through open-source participation.

### Success Metrics (first 6 months)
- **Traffic**: 2,000–5,000 unique visitors/month  
- **Engagement**: 500 newsletter signups; 100 template/download exports  
- **Early adoption**: 50+ users completing the self-assessment wizard  
- **Community traction**: 10+ external contributors engaging via PRs or Discussions  
- **Retention**: 30% of users returning to site tools monthly  

