## 4. [Scope & Features](#4-scope--features)
### 4.1 MVP Scope
- Resource Directory + Search
- Crosswalk Viewer (e.g., NIST ↔ CSA AICM ↔ OWASP LLM risks)
- Downloadable Templates (model/system cards, checklists)

### 4.2 Future Enhancements
- Self-Assessment Wizard (RMF maturity + roadmap)
- FAIR-based mini-risk quant tool
- Export APIs (CSV/JSON for compliance platforms)
- AI-Assistant Chatbot (post-launch)

---

## 5. [Requirements](#5-requirements)
### 5.1 Functional Requirements
- Browse and filter framework entries
- Interactive crosswalk UI
- Template generation & download
- Assessment tool with save/export

### 5.2 Non-Functional Requirements
- Responsive design, accessible content
- SEO-friendly & performance-optimized (Next.js + Vercel)
- Secure code and data handling

### 5.3 Technical Stack Highlights
- Frontend: Next.js, Tailwind CSS, Vercel hosting  
- Workflow: GitHub (repo/CI), Linear (tracking)  
- AI Tools: Cursor / Copilot (dev); optional chatbot using embedded doc search + LLM

---

## 6. [Assumptions, Dependencies & Risks](#6-assumptions-dependencies--risks)
- Assumes open-source documentation from NIST, CSA, ISO, etc., is accessible and licensable.
- Dependent on accuracy of incoming framework updates.
- Risk of hallucinations if chatbot added—mitigate with citations and source control.

